<BR>
56th Level Evoker<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzaknalfien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zaknalfien</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.iwdesign.net/ilsik/images/small_sig.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>4/20/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:28:59 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.iwdesign.net/ilsik/images/small_sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Suggestions for a Dark Elf Wiz</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I'm a dark elf wizard with my epic so I think I can answer this.<br>
<br>
You'll have ZERO problems in Erudin if you can find Camin without getting jumped by a guard. If you're 55+ with Sup Invis or just know the way you'll do it no problem. He's alone in a room and you can stand on your head and and break dance and nothing would agro on you.<br>
<br>
Dargon is a bit trickier, but if you pay attention to the guard paths (Superior Invis is also great here) you can find the gap in their pathing and be able to talk to Dargon/Arantir for 5 minutes while cowering behind a tree.<br>
<br>
There are 2 guards who's names I dont remember who path in front of the area where Arantir is. They will both come in from the left, pause in front of the alcove, move on, and return in a few minutes. They pause again in front of the alcove, then move on. If you see two guards do this, and both come in from the right (from behind Dargon) and stop, then move on, you know that you have aproximately 5 minutes before they return.<br>
<br>
If you're behind the tree you can buy potions, hand them in, talk to Arantir, and hand in the staffs all without agroing the nearby red KOS npc...just dont leave the tree.<br>
<br>
There is a safe spot around the corner from Dargon to the right, right next to a house between the house and a wall. I bound there and ran there when I got agro while testing out the paths of the guards and while buying potions, etc. I dont have a loc but you should be able to find it.<br>
<br>
Now...BE CAREFUL. Do your homework, be prepared. If you get agro while turning in the staffs for the love of GOD hit cancel; if you turn in some but not all, zone and come back, odds are you are SOL and you wont get your epic (story to that effect on this board)<br>
<br>
If you have any more questions I'll check back and try to answer them.</font><P><img src="http://www.iwdesign.net/ilsik/images/sig.jpg"><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toth</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>4/25/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:34:13 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Suggestions for a Dark Elf Wiz</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Just some added info to the above post from when I did it. While doing Halas I only encountered a guard in front of the shaman guild once. Perhaps I was just lucky to always pop in at the right times but I never once saw a guard anywhere near the shaman guild except that one time. When I saw him there he moved after about 10 seconds and didn't return while I was there. Also, Dargon will have no problem selling to you. I play a Dark Elf on a PvP server (I do take faction hits for PvP kills) and I've taken plenty of Barbarian faction hits and I had no problem with the quest.<br>
